Next, we consider another fundamental characteristics - the average translocation time. In accordance with the probabilities $P_{L(R)}$ studied in Figs.2-3, we separately calculated the average translocation times for the particles moving through the channel from the left to the right ($\tau_L$) and for those moving in the opposite direction ($\tau_R$). In simulations, we count the time each of simulated particles spends inside the channel. The average translocation time $\tau_L$ (or $\tau_R$) is then obtained by averaging these spending times over all the particles that passed through the channel from the left to the right (or from the right to the left). 

